# <type>[(<scope>)][!]: <description>   (title <= 50 chars, imperative,
#                                        lowercase start, no trailing period)
#
# type — first match wins:
#   revert   revert a prior commit
#   fix      correct wrong user-visible behavior      -> PATCH
#   feat     new user-visible behavior                -> MINOR
#   perf     measured performance improvement         -> PATCH
#   refactor restructure code, behavior unchanged
#   style    cosmetic only (whitespace, formatting)
#   test     tests only
#   docs     documentation only
#   build    build system or dependency changes
#   ci       CI pipeline configuration
#   chore    remaining maintenance
#
# scope — optional noun for the changed area: (auth), (parser)
# !     — before the colon marks a breaking change    -> MAJOR
#
# ------------------ blank line between title and body ------------------
# Body: wrap at 72 characters. Explain WHY, not HOW - the diff shows how.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Footers (each on its own line, after a blank line):
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <what breaks and how to migrate>
#   Closes #<issue>
#   Co-authored-by: Name <name@example.com>
